    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A brilliant red compound composed of mercuric iodide; it was used as a pigment briefly in the early 19th century. Iodine scarlet fades to yellow in sunlight and is highly toxic.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
